### Utility Functions

#### `ansi_supported()`

<div class="indented">
Checks if the current terminal supports ANSI escape codes. If the user is on Windows, this function also attempts to enable ANSI.

**`ansi_supported()` is only intended to be used if you arent using Kroma's color functions, and you are just using Kroma for checking if ANSI is supported. Kroma's style functions automatically check if ANSI is supported before applying styles, so you don't need to run it manually.**

**Returns:** `bool` - True if ANSI codes are supported, False otherwise

</div>

